{"questionId":"12268","questionHtml":"<p class=\"indent1\" style=\"margin-top:12pt;text-align:left;\">For the values of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\">\n  <mi>b</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;found in part (a), solve the system of linear equations</p>\n<p class=\"indent1\" style=\"margin-top:12pt;text-align:left;\"><span class=\"mjpage mjpage__block\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\" alttext=\"\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  {x + 2y - 2z = 5} \\\\   {3x + by + z = 0} \\\\   { - x + y - 3z = a - 1.}  \\end{array}\">\n  <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n          <mi>y</mi>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n          <mi>z</mi>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mn>5</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mi>b</mi>\n          <mi>y</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mi>z</mi>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mn>0</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mi>y</mi>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n          <mi>z</mi>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mn>1.</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n  </mtable>\n</math></span></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>the system is&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"BX = \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  5 \\\\   0 \\\\   6  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mi>B</mi>\n  <mi>X</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>5</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>6</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"X = \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  x \\\\   y \\\\   z  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mi>X</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mi>x</mi>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mi>y</mi>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mi>z</mi>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p>Then,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"X = A\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  5 \\\\   0 \\\\   6  \\end{array}} \\right) = \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  7&amp;{ - 4}&amp;{ - 6} \\\\   { - 8}&amp;5&amp;7 \\\\   { - 5}&amp;3&amp;4  \\end{array}} \\right)\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  5 \\\\   0 \\\\   6  \\end{array}} \\right).\">\n  <mi>X</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>5</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>6</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>7</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>4</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>6</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>8</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>5</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>7</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>5</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>4</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>5</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>6</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>.</mo>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>Thus&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = - 1\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = 2\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"z = - 1\">\n  <mi>z</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1) (C2)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12268","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.43b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"For the values of a and b found in part (a), solve the system of linear equations x + 2 y − 2 z = 5 3 x + b y + z = 0 − x + y − 3 z = a − 1.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Introduction to matrices"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}